oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Carter House kitchen
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior view of the Carter House kitchen located to the west of the main house.

The Carter House, a federal style brick home built in 1830 by Fountain Branch Carter, was taken over as the headquarters of the Twenty-Third Army Corps during the Second Battle of Franklin in the Civil War.
